SANITY ENVIRONMENT VARIABLESThe project ID and dataset are required to connect your Astro site to Sanity.You can find these in your Sanity project settings.Sanity project ID. It's safe to expose this on the client side.PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"Sanity dataset name. 'production' is the default. It's safe to expose this on the client side.PUBLIC_SANITY_DATASET="production"Sanity API version. Using the current date is a common practice. It's safe to expose this on the client side.PUBLIC_SANITY_API_VERSION="v2023-01-01"Sanity API token. This is used for authenticated requests, for example, to fetch draft content.This should be kept secret and is only used on the server (during the build process).It must NOT have a PUBLIC_ prefix.SANITY_API_TOKEN="your-api-token"To learn more about Sanity environment variables, check the documentation:https://www.sanity.io/docs/environment-variablesOptional: Netlify environment variablesYou might need these for specific Netlify features.For example, to trigger builds from Sanity webhooks.Example: Netlify build hook URL for Sanity webhooksNETLIFY_BUILD_HOOK_URL="your-netlify-build-hook-url"
